# 🚀 Automated Billing System (AWS + n8n + MySQL)

## 📌 Overview

This project implements an **automated billing system** using cloud infrastructure and workflow orchestration.

It retrieves users from a database, validates their status, creates customers (if needed), and generates recurring payments via an external payment API.



## 🏗️ Architecture

AWS EC2 (Docker + n8n)
        ↓
     MySQL (RDS)
        ↓
     Workflow (n8n)
        ↓
     Asaas API
        ↓
 Payment Generation (Boleto)



## ⚙️ Tech Stack

* AWS EC2 – Application hosting
* Docker – Containerization of n8n
* n8n – Workflow automation
* MySQL (RDS + EC2) – Database
* JavaScript – Data processing inside n8n
* Asaas API – Payment processing



# 🔄 Workflow Description

# 1. Scheduled Execution

* Runs monthly (day 5 at 12:00)

# 2. Data Retrieval

* Fetches all users from MySQL database

# 3. Processing Logic

* Iterates through users
* Filters only active clients
* Checks if `customer_id` exists

# 4. Customer Handling

* If customer exists → proceed
* If not → create customer via API

# 5. Due Date Calculation

* Supports multiple formats:

  * `YYYY-MM-DD`
  * `DD/MM/YYYY`
  * Day only (`DD`)
* Adjusts to next valid billing date

# 6. Payment Creation

* Generates boleto payment using API

# 7. Database Update

* Stores `customer_id` after creation



# 🧠 Key Features

* ✅ Automated billing workflow
* ✅ Conditional logic (active users only)
* ✅ Idempotent customer creation
* ✅ Dynamic date calculation
* ✅ API integration (REST)
* ✅ Batch processing (scalable)
* ✅ Data validation and sanitization


# 📊 Business Value

This system enables:

* Automated recurring billing
* Reduced manual operations
* Scalable payment processing
* Integration-ready architecture


